y-gaga-chromatica-album-review-2677590">&#39;Chromatica&#39;</a> and her <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-announces-joker-2-companion-album-harlequin-3796692"><em>Joker: Folie a Deux</em> companion record &#39;Harlequin&#39;</a> which was released last year.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Introducing <a href="https://twitter.com/ESPNF1?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@ESPNF1</a> &#39;s anthem for the 2025 season <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f37f.png" alt="🍿" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p><p> &#39;Garden of Eden&#39; by the one and only <a href="https://twitter.com/ladygaga?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@ladygaga</a> <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f929.png" alt="🤩" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <a href="https://t.co/INrpgyTO0r">pic.twitter.com/INrpgyTO0r</a></p><p> — ESPN (@espn) <a href="https://twitter.com/espn/status/1897286090135888180?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 5, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> Gaga also recently explained how &#39;Mayhem&#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-reveals-how-mayhem-differs-from-her-past-albums-3843786">differs from the rest of her back catalogue</a> .</p><p> In a new teaser for her interview with Lowe for Apple Music, Gaga said: “&#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/reviews-lady-gaga-14977-318026">Artpop</a> &#39; [2013] was a vibe. &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/lady-gaga-joanne-review-1759763">Joanne</a> &#39; [2016] was a sound, &#39;Chromatica&#39; [2020] had a sound all different [to the rest].</p><p> “&#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/reviews-lady-gaga-10984-316246">The Fame Monster</a> &#39; [2009] was more chaotic, &#39;The Fame&#39; [2008] was theatrical pop, &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/lady-gaga-born-this-way-review-778770">Born This Way</a> &#39; [2011], to me, had more of a metal-electro New York vibe to it,” she added. “So I actually made the effort when making &#39;Mayhem&#39; to not do that. Not try to give my music an outfit.”</p><p> As well as preparing for the release of the new album, Lady Gaga has also delighted fans in Mexico by announcing that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-announces-first-mexico-city-stadium-show-in-thirteen-years-3843267">she will be performing in the country for the first time in 13 years.</a></p><p> The pop icon will be taking over the Estadio GNP Seguros in Mexico City on April 26, and it is expected to see multiple songs performed from the &#39;Mayhem&#39; tracklist.</p><p> The news of that show came shortly after the &#39;Paparazzi&#39; hitmaker announced that she would be <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-announces-show-to-over-1million-fans-at-copacabana-beach-in-rio-3840268">performing a monumental free show to over a million fans at Copacabana Beach in Rio</a> .</p><p> In other news, Gaga is set to <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-to-celebrate-mayhem-release-by-pulling-double-duty-on-snl-3839233">pull double duty on <em>Saturday Night Live</em> (SNL) the day after &#39;Mayhem&#39;s launch</a> , where she will host the long-running sketch show and perform as a musical guest.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-previews-sassy-new-song-garden-of-eden-in-f1-advert-3843897">Lady Gaga previews sassy new song &#39;Garden Of Eden&#39; in F1 advert</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 Michael Sheen just paid £1m worth of debt for 900 people using his own money https://www.nme.com/news/film/michael-sheen-just-paid-1m-worth-of-debt-for-900-people-using-his-own-money-3843895?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=michael-sheen-just-paid-1m-worth-of-debt-for-900-people-using-his-own-moneyChris Edwards Wed, 05 Mar 2025 20:09:23 +0000 Film NewsNewsTV News https://www.nme.com/?p=3843895 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Michael Sheen" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> &quot;You need some help to get through these times&quot;</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/michael-sheen-just-paid-1m-worth-of-debt-for-900-people-using-his-own-money-3843895">Michael Sheen just paid £1m worth of debt for 900 people using his own money</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Michael Sheen" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Michael-Sheen-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/michael-sheen">Michael Sheen</a> has paid off £1 million of debt for 900 people using £100,000 of his own money.</p><p> The Welsh actor, known his for roles in <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/good-omens"><em>Good Omens</em></a> and the <em>Twilight</em> saga, used the £100,000 to start up a debt acquisition company to help the struggling individuals in his native south Wales.</p><p> The business venture is documented in an upcoming Channel 4 documentary titled <em>Michael Sheen&#39;s Secret Million Pound Giveaway</em> , which is set to air next week. The show aims to reveal how banks and finance companies are profiting from the country&#39;s most vulnerable.</p><p> “The shocking thing is that people have started having to use credit cards, overdrafts to pay for basics, to pay for necessities, rather than luxuries or anything like that, so the debt that I was able to buy included credit card debt, overdrafts, car finance, that kind of stuff,” said Sheen (via <a href="https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/michael-sheen-show-wales-debt-channel-4-secret-million-pound-giveaway-1236155260/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Hollywood Reporter</em></a> ).</p><p> “You need some help to get through these times. And people are getting into spirals of debt. Once you&#39;re underwater it&#39;s very hard to get out again. That&#39;s why I wanted to do this — to draw attention to the fact that this is going on, and there is a way to change it, there are alternatives, and we need to push to try and make a difference for people.” </p><figure id="attachment_2534184" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2534184" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-2534184" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2019_michaelsheen_2000x1270.jpg" alt="Michael Sheen" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2019_michaelsheen_2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2019_michaelsheen_2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2019_michaelsheen_2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2019_michaelsheen_2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2019_michaelsheen_2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2019_michaelsheen_2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-2534184" class="wp-caption-text"> Michael Sheen.图片来源：盖蒂图像</figcaption></figure><p>Appearing on <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/bbc">BBC</a> &#39;s <em>The One Show</em> on Wednesday (March 5), Sheen said he was initially cautious about using his money to start up the debt acquisition company. The actor said he doesn&#39;t have £100,000 to “throw around” and therefore wanted the project to be “effective”.</p><p> It was only after he met a woman in a Port Talbot cafe, who told him about “steelworkers in tears”, that he decided to go ahead with the company. The actor&#39;s venture comes five months after the closure of a blast furnace in Wales, marking the end of traditional steelworking in the Port Talbot region, which lead to a widespread loss of jobs.</p><p> In recent months, Sheen also self-financed a new national theatre to replace the National Theatre Wales, which was forced to close in 2024 due to £1.6 million funding cut.</p><p>这位演员说，威尔士国家剧院的关闭“令人难以置信的悲伤，但并不令人惊讶”，这激发了他找到解决方案。 “[I realised] if we don&#39;t find a way to reimagine the way forward, it may be a long time — if ever — that we have the opportunity to have a national theatre in Wales again.</p><p> “I want it to be something that represents the rich culture that we are and always have been in this country.” he added, explaining that the company is now seeking private and public funding but self-financing will allow the theatre to stand “on its own two feet.”</p><p> Sheen is reprising his role as Aziraphale in the third and final season of <em>Good Omens</em> , which <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/good-omens-to-wrap-with-one-final-episode-instead-of-full-series-following-neil-gaiman-accusations-3805990">will now premiere as a single 90-minute episode</a> instead of a full series. The final instalment will be available to stream on <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/amazon-prime-video">Amazon Prime Video</a> , but a release date has not yet been set.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/michael-sheen-just-paid-1m-worth-of-debt-for-900-people-using-his-own-money-3843895">Michael Sheen just paid £1m worth of debt for 900 people using his own money</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
